[[!meta title="Energy Drink — Red Bull Spring Edition Cherry Sakura Sugarfree"]]
[[!tag Energy_Drink Review]]

If there is one company that continually innovates on how an energy drink can
taste, it is Red Bull. They've released seasonal editions at a rapid pace
recently. I feel like I only just tried this Winter's
[[Red_Bull_Winter_Edition_Fuji_Apple_Ginger_Sugarfree]] and
[[Red_Bull_Winter_Edition_Fuji_Apple_Ginger_Sugarfree]] and now we're already on
to the Spring edition? And I'm always very impressed with the palette of flavors
they are able to synthesize with every new edition with such quick turnaround
and at such a scale.

<figure>
[[!template id="hooya-img.tmpl" cid="bafkreif5ntkotgxi75tlttnpgymcsprjwt4fcfnalyq67fwz4m3miotm6a" size=medium]]
</figure>

This year's Spring edition has a surprisingly complex profile. The taste is
light and airy yet grounded with botanical and subtle citrus notes. As this one
is sugarfree, it lacks the body of typical Red Bulls. The empty, vapid finish
of artifical sweeteners perfectly suits this light drink. Considering how bitter
caffeine is, this drink masks it beautifully.

Not my favorite from Red Bull, but this year's Spring Edition is yet another Red
Bull banger.
